This results from the help command's context preventing the use of `ctx.cog`.

Here's a minimal example that demostrates the issue. When the help formatter is called, ctx.cog is None so an exception is thrown. It would be nice to have a way to access the "original" cog. I checked the rewrite branch too and there didn't seem to be a way to do this yet.

```
from discord.ext import commands

def is_authorized():
    def predicate(ctx):
        if ctx.message.author.id in ctx.cog.admin_user_ids:
            return True

        return False

    return commands.check(predicate)

class Admin:
    """
    Commands available for admins only
    """

    def __init__(self, bot, admin_user_ids):
        self.bot = bot
        self.admin_user_ids = admin_user_ids

    @commands.command()
    @is_authorized()
    async def hey(self):
        await self.bot.reply("Hey!")

```
