The sortAppend configuration is not documented except in the code file.  The sortForce configuration parrameter is documented as "appending an additional sort order".  However it seems the sortForce parameter "prepends" a sort order and the sortAppend configuration is not used in the code.  I think this is a bug.  it is easilly fixed by adding the following code to line 752:

                                // append forced column to sort list 
                                if (config.sortAppend != null) {
                                    var a = config.sortAppend;
                                    for (var j = 0; j < a.length; j++) {
                                        if (a[j][0] != i) {
                                            config.sortList.push(a[j]);
                                        }
                                    }
                                } 

I have added this and tested it in my code.  Happy to pull and correct if my analysis is correct.

